<TITLE> JS contestants must file returns by Jan 31 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)  All contestants in the ninth parliamentary election must submit their election expenses returns by Jan 31 (Saturday) or face fines and possible prison terms, said election officials on Wednesday. "There is provision for jail sentences of 2-7 years and fines if the contestants fail to comply with the orders," Farhad Ahmed Khan told bdnews24.com on Wednesday. "The deputy commissioners and returning officers and district election officials have been notified about the directives," said the EC senior assistant secretary. The offices of returning officers and other concerned election officials will remain open on Jan 30 and 31 (Friday and Saturday) to ease filing of the returns by prescribed forms, in person or by registered mails, said Farhad. According to the Representation of the People Order, all contestants must file their election expense returns within 30 days of results being published by gazette. "In that case all those who contested the Dec 29 general election, except those of the deferred Noakhali-1 poll, will have to submit the expenses returns by Jan 31." Political parties must submit their expenditure returns within 90 days of the results, he added. EC deputy secretary Mihir Sarwar Morshed said the general secretaries or secretaries general of 38 political parties had already been notified that they would have to file their returns by Mar 31. The results of the Dec 29 national election were gazetted on Jan 1. Some 1,567 candidates including 1,426 from 38 political parties took part. The remaining 151 were independent candidates. bdnews
